parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause inconsistent braking pressure, hesitation to stop, and increased stopping distance, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Inconsistent braking pressure
severe brake pedal modulation required to stop the vehicle
hesitation to stop
squawk noise when depressing the brake pedal
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake lamps may not trigger until the vehicle has come to a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of braking ability, increased stopping distance, and accidents, which can lead to injuries and fatalities.
symptoms: Brake pedal requires significant force to trigger brake lamps
brake lamps may not trigger until the vehicle has come to a complete stop
brake failure resulting in accidents
loud squealing or grabbing and shuddering of brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster pump can cause premature failure of the brake system, leading to increased stopping distance and accidents.
symptoms: Brake booster pump overheating
brake system failure
increased stopping distance
accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when the vehicle is traveling at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and violently accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle accelerates even when the driver is braking
the vehicle continues to accelerate even when the driver shifts into neutral or park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake pedal position sensor can cause the vehicle's electronic throttle control system to malfunction, leading to unintended acceleration, which can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and violently accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle accelerates even when the driver is braking
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brake lights do not illuminate when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning electronic throttle control system can cause unintended acceleration, which can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and violently accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle accelerates even when the driver is braking
the engine RPM surges or fluctuates erratically
the vehicle's speedometer and tachometer readings are inaccurate.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inaccurate Child Car Seat Installation Instructions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrect child car seat installation instructions in the owner's manual can lead to improper installation, which can increase the risk of injury or death to children in the event of an accident.
symptoms: None
as this issue is related to the instructions provided by the manufacturer rather than a malfunction of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, create a hazardous driving environment, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries from flying glass fragments.
symptoms: Sudden loud noise
similar to a shotgun blast
while driving; discovery of a large hole in the sunroof; presence of glass fragments on the visor or interior surfaces; no external damage or marks on the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective sunroof design or manufacturing process can lead to spontaneous shattering, causing a hazardous driving environment and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loud noise
similar to a shotgun blast
while driving; discovery of a large hole in the sunroof; presence of glass fragments on the visor or interior surfaces; no external damage or marks on the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, resulting in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the steering wheel seizes
the brake pedal travels down to the floorboard and fails to stop the vehicle
the vehicle crashes into obstacles or other vehicles.
